<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🏭 RB003 Week 8 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Ship It — Publish &amp; Present · <strong>Course:</strong> Tycoon Engineer · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>This week you <strong>publish</strong> your tycoon so anyone can play it, then present your work.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each one. Before you imagine it happening, circle or write your answer.</p>
<pre><code>Game Settings → Permissions
Playability: Private
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Your friend clicks your game link. Can they play? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p><strong>Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-lua">store:SetAsync(player.UserId, cash.Value)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Your saving script works. You earn 200 cash, leave, and join again. Is your cash still 200? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>Each pair shows the right way first, then a broken version of the same idea. Circle what's different and write one short sentence about the bug.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — Friends should be able to join your game.</p>
<pre><code>-- clean
Playability: Public
</code></pre>
<pre><code>-- buggy
Playability: Private
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Who can play the buggy version?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — Friends should see your <strong>newest</strong> version.</p>
<pre><code>-- clean
1. Change your prices
2. File → Publish to Roblox
</code></pre>
<pre><code>-- buggy
1. Change your prices
2. Close Studio
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Which version do your friends see in the buggy steps?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>To test saving in Studio, one setting must be on. One word is missing. Fill it in using the word bank.</p>
<pre><code>Game Settings → Security
[✓] Enable Studio Access to API ____
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>Services</code> · <code>Parts</code> · <code>Friends</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing word:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now publish your tycoon: give it a <strong>name</strong> and an <strong>icon</strong>, and set it to <strong>Public</strong>. Then play your published game — earn cash, leave, rejoin, and check your cash is still there.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of your game's page, then explain. Use these sentence starters — write 2 or 3 sentences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My game is called …</p>
<p>My favorite part is …</p>
<p>The hardest bug was …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) — this is your <strong>presentation</strong>. Talk like you are showing your game to a new player. Try to use these words: <strong>publish</strong>, <strong>public</strong>, <strong>upgrade</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your game's page — its name and icon.</li>
<li>Play: earn cash and buy one upgrade.</li>
<li>Leave and rejoin — show your cash is still there.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> You can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
